headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; The Academy of Medicina--Yellow Fever--Education of Idiots, &c. SUPREME COURT--SPECIAL TERM.

docs.lead_paragraph: The regular monthly meeting of the Academy of Medicine was held on Monday evening, at the University, Dr. WATSON, Vice-President, and subsequently, Dr. W. PARKER, President, in the Chair. The Section on Public Health made a report through Dr. GRISOON, Chairman, as ordered by the Academy at the August meeting, on the relation of yellow fever to New-York City.

headline.main: Fremont and Dayton Central Club.; Enthusiastic Reception of the Amended Returns from Pennsyvania. Large Meeting at the Tabernacle.

docs.lead_paragraph: A large respectable meeting of the mumbers the Young Men's Fremont and Dayton Central club, and of the friends of the Republfean ?? generally, was held last night at the Tabernacle, The President,in announcing the names of the speakers present,and of thous who were oxpected, stated amid much applauso that ?? LAW would certinly be in the bulding in time to addrress the audience if his health would permit.

headline.main: ONE WEEK LATER FROM EUROPE.; ARRIVAL OF THE PERSIA. Threatening Aspect of the Neapolitan Question. Interferense of Russia in Behalf of Naples. IMPORTANT TRADE ??ND MONEY NEWS. docs.lead_paragraph: The British Mail steamer Persia, Capt. JUNKINS, from Liverpool (soon after) 11 o' clock A. M. of Saturday, the 4th, arrived at her dock yesterday morning. The City of Baltimore arrived at Liverpool 1 1/2 o'clock A.M. of Wednesday, the 1st; and the Cambria at 1 'o clock P.M. of Thursday, the 4th October. The Ericsson Sailed from Liverpool Wednesday, the 1st, for New-York. The Fullon arrived at Southampton on Friday night, the 3d inst.
